‚∏ª

AI Agent Rules (IMPORTANT)

Additional constraints apply when an issue is executed by an AI agent:
	‚Ä¢	AI agents must follow:
	‚Ä¢	contributing_issue_codingworkflow
	‚Ä¢	AI agents must not infer missing intent
	‚Ä¢	If the Intent section is missing or unclear:
	‚Ä¢	The AI agent must stop
	‚Ä¢	A clarification or proposal issue must be created

‚∏ª

Recommendations (Explicitly Optional)

The following sections are recommended, not required:
	‚Ä¢	Acceptance criteria
	‚Ä¢	Known risks or edge cases
	‚Ä¢	Non-goals
	‚Ä¢	Related issues or epics

Optional sections must be clearly marked as such.

‚∏ª

General Principles
	‚Ä¢	Short and clear beats detailed and vague
	‚Ä¢	One well-scoped issue is better than many tiny ones
	‚Ä¢	Use epics for coordination, not bureaucracy
	‚Ä¢	If an AI agent cannot confidently execute the issue, the issue is invalid
